---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Disclaimer — HelixVault"
  description="Important disclaimer: HelixVault provides educational research content only. Nothing on this site constitutes medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative pt-16 pb-10 md:pt-24 md:pb-14 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0" style="
      background:
        radial-gradient(ellipse at 15% 50%, oklch(0.62 0.16 192 / 0.08), transparent 50%),
        linear-gradient(to bottom, oklch(0.13 0.010 250), oklch(0.11 0.008 250));
    "></div>
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 right-0 h-[2px]" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent 0%, oklch(0.62 0.16 192 / 0.6) 40%, transparent 100%);"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-display text-surface-800/40 mb-8">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-400 transition-colors">Home</a>
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" class="w-3 h-3">
          <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.22 5.22a.75.75 0 0 1 1.06 0l4.25 4.25a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.06l-4.25 4.25a.75.75 0 0 1-1.06-1.06L11.94 10 8.22 6.28a.75.75 0 0 1 0-1.06Z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
        </svg>
        <span class="text-surface-800/60">Disclaimer</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight font-display text-surface-950 mb-4">Disclaimer</h1>
      <p class="text-sm font-display text-surface-800/40">Last updated: January 2025</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <article class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose-dark">

        <h2>Educational and Research Purposes Only</h2>
        <p>
          HelixVault ("we," "us," "our") is a research resource website that provides educational information about peptides and related scientific literature. All content published on HelixVault — including articles, guides, summaries, and any other materials — is intended solely for general educational and informational purposes.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Nothing on this website constitutes medical advice, medical diagnosis, or medical treatment.</strong> The information provided should never be used as a substitute for the advice, diagnosis, or treatment of a qualified, licensed healthcare professional.
        </p>

        <h2>No Doctor-Patient Relationship</h2>
        <p>
          Use of HelixVault does not create a doctor-patient relationship or any other professional-client relationship. We are not physicians, pharmacists, nurses, or any other licensed healthcare professionals. Any information you read here should be discussed with a qualified healthcare provider before you take any action.
        </p>

        <h2>Research Status of Compounds Discussed</h2>
        <p>
          Many of the compounds discussed on HelixVault are research chemicals that are not approved by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) or equivalent regulatory bodies in other jurisdictions for human therapeutic use. These compounds may be illegal to purchase, possess, or use in certain countries. It is your sole responsibility to understand and comply with all applicable laws in your jurisdiction.
        </p>
        <p>
          The fact that we discuss a compound does not constitute an endorsement, recommendation, or encouragement to obtain or use it. We discuss these compounds in the context of their scientific literature only.
        </p>

        <h2>Accuracy of Information</h2>
        <p>
          We make reasonable efforts to ensure that the information on HelixVault is accurate and reflects the current state of scientific literature. However, scientific understanding evolves rapidly, and not all information may be current at the time of reading. We make no warranties or representations, express or implied, about the completeness, accuracy, reliability, suitability, or availability of any information on this site.
        </p>
        <p>
          Studies and research cited on this site reflect findings from academic literature, which may include animal studies, in vitro studies, or preliminary human trials. Such findings may not translate to real-world human outcomes. Correlation in research settings does not imply causation in clinical practice.
        </p>

        <h2>Not a Substitute for Professional Advice</h2>
        <p>
          Always seek the advice of a physician, pharmacist, or other qualified health provider with any questions you may have regarding a medical condition, medication, supplement, or health decision. Never disregard professional medical advice or delay seeking it because of something you have read on this website.
        </p>

        <h2>Links to External Sources</h2>
        <p>
          HelixVault may link to external websites, including PubMed, academic journals, and other third-party sources. These links are provided for convenience and reference only. We have no control over the content of those sites and accept no responsibility for them or for any loss or damage that may arise from your use of them.
        </p>

        <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, HelixVault and its operators shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, special, or punitive damages arising from your use of, or reliance on, any content on this website. This includes, without limitation, damages for personal injury, property damage, lost profits, or any other pecuniary loss.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this disclaimer or about how we present scientific information, you may reach us at: <a href="mailto:research@helixvault.onrender.com">research@helixvault.onrender.com</a>
        </p>

      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-surface-200/20">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold font-display text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300 transition-colors">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" class="w-4 h-4">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10.5 19.5 3 12m0 0 7.5-7.5M3 12h18" />
          </svg>
          Back to home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

</Base>
